==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mainspring
<hw>main"spring`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The principal or
most important spring in a piece of mechanism, especially the moving
spring of a watch or clock or the spring in a gunlock which impels the
hammer.</def> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>(Fig.)</mark> <def>The chief
or most powerful motive; the efficient cause of action; <as>as, the
<ex>mainspring</ex> of action</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mainstay</ent>⟦br⟧
